laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive result for IgG against herpes simplex and rubella virus.
Patchy and slightly longer T2 signals in the white matter of both parietal lobes and slightly increased extra-cerebral space in both frontotemporal regions.
Slightly slower background rhythm, with no epileptic waves detected.
One pathogenic variant of MAP2K1 and two pathogenic variants with unclear significance (ATP2B3 and CDC42BPB).
